dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:speech_to_text/speech_to_text.dart' as stt;
import 'package:flutter_tts/flutter_tts.dart';
import 'dart:convert';
import 'package:http/http.dart' as http;

void main() {
  runApp(const SynthApp());
}

class SynthApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const SynthApp({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      home: SynthHome(),
      debugShowCheckedModeBanner: false,
    );
  }
}

class SynthHome extends StatefulWidget {
  @override
  State<SynthHome> createState() => _SynthHomeState();
}

class _SynthHomeState extends State<SynthHome> {
  // Speech to Text
  final stt.SpeechToText _speech = stt.SpeechToText();
  bool isListening = false;
  String userSpeech = "";

  // Text to Speech
  final FlutterTts tts = FlutterTts();

  // Video Output URL (placeholder)
  String? generatedVideoUrl;

  // ---- Initialize TTS ----
  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    tts.setSpeechRate(0.4);
  }

  // ---- Start Listening ----
  Future<void> startListening() async {
    bool available = await _speech.initialize();
    if (available) {
      setState(() {
        isListening = true;
      });
      _speech.listen(onResult: (result) {
        setState(() {
          userSpeech = result.recognizedWords;
        });
      });
    }
  }

  // ---- Stop Listening ----
  Future<void> stopListening() async {
    setState(() {
      isListening = false;
    });
    _speech.stop();
  }

  // ---- Text to Speech ----
  Future speak(String text) async {
    await tts.speak(text);
  }

  // ---- Send Voice â†’ Video (placeholder API call) ----
  Future<void> generateVideoFromVoice() async {
    if (userSpeech.isEmpty) return;

    // This will later call OpenAI/GAIAgrid backend
    final response = await http.post(
      Uri.parse("https://your-api.com/generate-video"),
      headers: {"Content-Type": "application/json"},
      body: jsonEncode({"prompt": userSpeech}),
    );

    if (response.statusCode == 200) {
      setState(() {
        generatedVideoUrl = jsonDecode(response.body)["video_url"];
      });
    }
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      backgroundColor: Colors.black,
      body: SafeArea(
        child: Padding(
          padding: const EdgeInsets.all(20),
          child: Column(
            children: [
              const Text(
                "The Synth\nVoice â†’ Intelligence â†’ Reality",
                textAlign: TextAlign.center,
                style: TextStyle(
                  fontSize: 28,
                  color: Colors.white,
                  fontWeight: FontWeight.bold,
                ),
              ),

              const SizedBox(height: 30),

              // Speech Results
              Container(
                padding: const EdgeInsets.all(16),
                decoration: BoxDecoration(
                  color: Colors.white12,
                  borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(12),
                ),
                child: Text(
                  userSpeech.isEmpty ? "Say somethingâ€¦" : userSpeech,
                  style: const TextStyle(color: Colors.white, fontSize: 18),
                ),
              ),

              const SizedBox(height: 20),

              // Record button
              GestureDetector(
                onTap: () {
                  isListening ? stopListening() : startListening();
                },
                child: CircleAvatar(
                  radius: 45,
                  backgroundColor: isListening ? Colors.red : Colors.blue,
                  child: Icon(
                    Icons.mic,
                    color: Colors.white,
                    size: 40,
                  ),
                ),
              ),

              const SizedBox(height: 20),

              // Speak back
              ElevatedButton(
                onPressed: () => speak(userSpeech),
                child: const Text("Speak Response"),
              ),

              const SizedBox(height: 20),

              // Generate video from voice
              ElevatedButton(
                onPressed: generateVideoFromVoice,
                child: const Text("Generate Video From Voice"),
              ),

              const SizedBox(height: 20),

              if (generatedVideoUrl != null)
                Text(
                  "Video generated:\n$generatedVideoUrl",
                  style: const TextStyle(color: Colors.greenAccent),
                  textAlign: TextAlign.center,
                ),
            ],
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}

--- STEP 6: REAL-TIME AVATAR STREAMING ---
console.log('Flutter client connected');

let pc = new RTCPeerConnection();

pc.onicecandidate = (event) => {
if (event.candidate) {
ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'ice', candidate: event.candidate }));
}
};

// In a real system: attach avatar video track here
// For demo: create placeholder video track using canvas capture or media file

ws.on('message', async (msg) => {
const data = JSON.parse(msg);

if (data.type === 'offer') {
await pc.setRemoteDescription(new RTCSessionDescription(data.offer));
const answer = await pc.createAnswer();
await pc.setLocalDescription(answer);
ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'answer', answer }));
} else if (data.type === 'candidate') {
await pc.addIceCandidate(data.candidate);
}
});

ws.on('close', () => {
pc.close();
console.log('Flutter client disconnected');
});
});

# Step 6 â€” Real-Time Avatar Streaming

## Goal
Connect AI Avatar Engine (Step 5) with Flutter app for live WebRTC streaming.

## Steps
1. Start AI Avatar Engine: `node backend/avatar_engine.js`
2. Start WebRTC Avatar Server: `node backend/avatar_webrtc_server.js`
3. In Flutter app, initialize WebRTCAvatarService:

```dart
final avatarService = WebRTCAvatarService();
await avatarService.initConnection();
```

4. Send offer SDP to server via WebSocket.
5. Server responds with answer SDP; set it using `setRemoteDescription`.
6. Listen for ICE candidates from server and add them using `addCandidate`.
7. Display remote avatar stream with `AvatarWebRTCView` widget.
